EDUCATIONAL USE & ETHICAL HACKING DISCLAIMER
===============================================================================

This repository contains educational material related to cybersecurity,
penetration testing, and ethical hacking. ALL CONTENT is provided for
EDUCATIONAL PURPOSES ONLY.

STRICT CONDITIONS OF USE:

1. AUTHORIZED USE ONLY
   - Use this material ONLY on systems you own or have explicit written
     permission to test
   - Unauthorized access to computer systems is ILLEGAL worldwide
   - Always obtain proper authorization before conducting any security testing

2. CONTROLLED ENVIRONMENTS
   - All demonstrations, labs, and scripts should be executed in isolated,
     controlled environments (personal VMs, authorized labs, CTF platforms)
   - NEVER use these tools or techniques on production systems without
     proper authorization

3. RESPONSIBLE DISCLOSURE
   - If you discover vulnerabilities using knowledge from this repository,
     follow responsible disclosure practices
   - Report vulnerabilities to the appropriate parties before public disclosure
   - Never exploit vulnerabilities for malicious purposes

4. NO WARRANTY
   - The author provides NO WARRANTY for the accuracy, completeness, or
     effectiveness of any material in this repository
   - Use at your own risk

5. LIABILITY
   - The author is NOT responsible for:
     * Any misuse of the information or tools provided
     * Any illegal activities conducted using this material
     * Any damage caused by the use of this material
   - Users take FULL RESPONSIBILITY for their actions

6. LEGAL COMPLIANCE
   - Users must comply with ALL applicable laws and regulations including:
     * Computer Fraud and Abuse Act (CFAA) - USA
     * Marco Civil da Internet (Lei 12.965/2014) - Brazil
     * Lei Geral de Proteção de Dados (LGPD) - Brazil
     * Council of Europe Convention on Cybercrime
     * All local and international cybersecurity laws

7. ETHICAL CONDUCT
   - Follow the ethical guidelines of the cybersecurity community
   - Respect privacy and confidentiality
   - Never cause intentional harm or disruption
   - Promote security awareness and education

VIOLATION WARNING:
Violation of these conditions or applicable laws may result in:
